Section 1:
1 L.D. 1823
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 JUDICIARY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 710, L.D. 1823, “An Act to Promote
10 Transparency in the Criminal Justice System by Requiring the Posting of Criminal Case
11 Decisions”
12 Amend the bill by inserting after the title and before the enacting clause the following:
13 'Mandate preamble. This measure requires one or more local units of government
14 to expand or modify activities so as to necessitate additional expenditures from local
15 revenues but does not provide funding for at least 90% of those expenditures. Pursuant to
16 the Constitution of Maine, Article IX, Section 21, 2/3 of all of the members elected to each
17 House have determined it necessary to enact this measure.'
18 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 313 in §2401 in the first indented paragraph in the last
19 6 lines (page 1, lines 8 to 13 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "A clerk of the District
20 Court or a clerk of the Superior Court shall post to that clerk's publicly accessible website
21 the final decision of a criminal case decided within that prosecutorial district within 60 days
22 of the case's final disposition. A clerk of the Unified Criminal Docket, as defined in section
23 1003, subsection 11, shall post to the clerk's publicly accessible website the final decision
24 of a criminal case decided within the State within 60 days of the case's final disposition"
25 and inserting the following: 'A district attorney shall post to the publicly accessible website
26 of the county the district attorney represents the final decision of a criminal case decided
27 within that district attorney's prosecutorial district within 60 days of the case's final
28 disposition'
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment strikes the requirement that a clerk of the District Court, Superior
3333 Court and Unified Criminal Docket post to a publicly accessible website the final
3344 disposition of a criminal case within 60 days of the case's final disposition and replaces it
3355 with a requirement that a district attorney post the same information to the publicly
Page 1 - 132LR1968(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 710, L.D. 1823
316 accessible website of the county the district attorney represents within 60 days of the case's
327 final disposition. It also adds a mandate preamble.
338 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
349 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR1968(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
